physical_examinations.vital_signs: High white-cell counts: 28,200 per cubic millimeter in Patient III-1; 20,400 per cubic millimeter in Patient III-5.
physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Marrow was hypercellular in Patient III-1 with 30 percent myeloperoxidase-positive blast cells; marrow was normocellular in Patient III-5 with 35 percent myeloperoxidase-positive blast cells.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Both patients had an increase in leukocytes primarily due to neutrophilia, which resolved without medical intervention.

physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Both patients entered complete remission after the first course of combination chemotherapy.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Currently, more than 20 months since diagnosis, both patients are well and have normal blood counts.
